10/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU Police Mission to BiH released a statement Tuesday (9 September) saying that the crime rate in the country remained relatively stable during the first seven months of the year. There was a 2 per cent increase in crimes compared to the same period last year, but 29 per cent more arrests. The mission concludes that local police are performing "professionally".
In other news Tuesday, the Republika Srpska Defence Ministry announced it received ten offers to purchase excess weapons and military equipment. The ministry will officially open bids on 15 September. Also Tuesday, SFOR troops said they discovered 12 large and several smaller arms caches in Prijedor. (Onasa, BHTV 1, SRNA, BBC - 09/09/03)
